<subSubSection id="2FC7BDA6899A67FAE1D7ABD0DB35E3CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8D5C41257AA7FA7E296C0923191E1A66" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CAEDA76DB37A1E98FE7B13B1C29C1760" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
Widespread in the West Indies, also reported from Mexico, Ecuador, Chile, and has recently dispersed (probably via accidental human introduction) to French Polynesia and Tonga (
<bibRefCitation id="5753BA8C406B785AEB5EAFDCBEF97231" author="Bickel, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum Occasional Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="14 - 20" refId="B6" refString="Bickel, DJ, 2000. New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Bishop Museum Occasional Papers 64: 14 - 20" title="New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." volume="64" year="2000">Bickel 2000</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="40A268FA71A10D70A76C8CBE5C7F373A" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="866B2F87281A0E84672E21817B2A28DC" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CA3CD8DD85DB56BFE697777246A15A16" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">
<bibRefCitation id="70CEA6B853108A9E96D0AD9DCD732595" author="Aldrich, JM" journalOrPublisher="Kansas University Science Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="75 - 94" refId="B3" refString="Aldrich, JM, 1902. Dolichopodidae of Grenada, W.I. Kansas University Science Bulletin 1: 75 - 94" title="Dolichopodidae of Grenada, W. I." volume="1" year="1902">Aldrich (1902)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="8444244CF07E9372607C6367369E77BF" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Achradocera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Achradocera apicalis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="46CD94440455ECA01D9C31F7C1DE4545" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Achradocera apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Aldrich) with 
<taxonomicName id="01C270922F8C9504C326A71CCAAAFC20" genus="A." lsidName="A. barbata" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="barbata">
<emphasis id="BFACEFA79A6D4E224696207A739E47DE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. barbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Loew), primarily due to the distinctive femoral coloration of both species. 
<bibRefCitation id="5A6FB45E811331EF67284243000F1764" DOI="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" author="Robinson, H" journalOrPublisher="Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="1 - 141" refId="B67" refString="Robinson, H, 1975. Bredin-Archbold-Smithsonian Biological Survey of Dominica, the family Dolichopodidae with some related Antillean and Panamanian species (Diptera). Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 185: 1 - 141, DOI: https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" title="Bredin-Archbold-Smithsonian Biological Survey of Dominica, the family Dolichopodidae with some related Antillean and Panamanian species (Diptera)." url="https://doi.org/10.5479/si.00810282.185" volume="185" year="1975">Robinson (1975)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName id="07DE597331F9FEED67B2EF38BA80E06D" genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="9E393D057B2E7C4CA092DCF8EDC6C85E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
distinct by the much shorter antenna of the male. 
<bibRefCitation id="96CADDC59A269EABEA2E75F20C7850BF" author="Bickel, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum Occasional Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="14 - 20" refId="B6" refString="Bickel, DJ, 2000. New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Bishop Museum Occasional Papers 64: 14 - 20" title="New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." volume="64" year="2000">Bickel (2000)</bibRefCitation>
followed 
<bibRefCitation id="8EA7B6F6001CC511897AAB8BB8853AE7" author="Aldrich, JM" journalOrPublisher="Kansas University Science Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="75 - 94" refId="B3" refString="Aldrich, JM, 1902. Dolichopodidae of Grenada, W.I. Kansas University Science Bulletin 1: 75 - 94" title="Dolichopodidae of Grenada, W. I." volume="1" year="1902">Aldrich (1902)</bibRefCitation>
and treated 
<taxonomicName id="92D69D355E38647661A8E5202C4EFFFD" genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="343D53074D66FA0FE50489AC1163A757" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2E81604461BB2080411F679C68507925" genus="A." lsidName="A. barbata" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="barbata">
<emphasis id="DC36650BE9BBADD5C81E5A4D02D63C6A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. barbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as synonyms, based again in part on femoral coloration and variation in male antennal length. However, comparison of photos of the holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="EF422CDC2597D5E8F8A7D3C12572EF18" genus="A." lsidName="A. barbata" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="barbata">
<emphasis id="2D89B96E99CB29E3C610D0FB822EDE59" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. barbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(MCZ) and specimens from North America (Alabama, Florida, Georgia, Indiana, Kentucky, Missouri, New York, Pennsylvania, Texas, South Carolina, Virginia) with 
<taxonomicName id="395C8FAC6AF4C762C9245BB8BBA638AA" genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="F97530EE636FE3CEDBD8E2C08C403684" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the West Indies (Dominica, Montserrat, Nevis, St. Lucia, St. Vincent) reveals that these species are distinct, most notably in the form of the male front tarsus and genitalia (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7B5A9C3F748FB6BF86DB749065B7F8C8" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Tarsus I and terminalia of males A Achradocera apicalis (Aldrich), tarsus I, posterior view (Montserrat) B Achradocera barbata (Loew), tarsus I, posterior view (Kentucky, USA), arrows indicate ventral setae C Achradocera apicalis, tip of abdomen, left lateral (Montserrat) D Achradocera barbata, tip of abdomen, left lateral (Florida, USA). Scale bars: 0.25 mm (A, B), 0.5 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.966.55192.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450942" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">18</figureCitation>
). The 
<taxonomicName id="00CE2BD0C38683A6476DFC21C69429A6" genus="A." lsidName="A. barbata" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="barbata">
<emphasis id="B84BC579E8B7C45EB64CB161F2ED1A38" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. barbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
type and male specimens from North America all have a distinct series of ventral setae on tarsus I (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="ADD691C86DE8D8BE74D15D98A9D6F707" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Tarsus I and terminalia of males A Achradocera apicalis (Aldrich), tarsus I, posterior view (Montserrat) B Achradocera barbata (Loew), tarsus I, posterior view (Kentucky, USA), arrows indicate ventral setae C Achradocera apicalis, tip of abdomen, left lateral (Montserrat) D Achradocera barbata, tip of abdomen, left lateral (Florida, USA). Scale bars: 0.25 mm (A, B), 0.5 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.966.55192.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450942" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">18B</figureCitation>
) whereas specimens from the West Indies (including syntypes from St. Vincent) lack these setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="1CAD87F352CA05C3A6178E48C3C07F3A" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Tarsus I and terminalia of males A Achradocera apicalis (Aldrich), tarsus I, posterior view (Montserrat) B Achradocera barbata (Loew), tarsus I, posterior view (Kentucky, USA), arrows indicate ventral setae C Achradocera apicalis, tip of abdomen, left lateral (Montserrat) D Achradocera barbata, tip of abdomen, left lateral (Florida, USA). Scale bars: 0.25 mm (A, B), 0.5 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.966.55192.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450942" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">18A</figureCitation>
). The surstylus and phallus are also very different, with 
<taxonomicName id="9AFDB251A6F0741540E5E8F20B38051A" genus="A." lsidName="A. barbata" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="barbata">
<emphasis id="F800F14116EF35AA6EFD95390C3A5008" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. barbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
having the surstylus enlarged and rounded apically and phallus dorsally serrate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="946BE8559B25A0E76D54B371951FF238" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Tarsus I and terminalia of males A Achradocera apicalis (Aldrich), tarsus I, posterior view (Montserrat) B Achradocera barbata (Loew), tarsus I, posterior view (Kentucky, USA), arrows indicate ventral setae C Achradocera apicalis, tip of abdomen, left lateral (Montserrat) D Achradocera barbata, tip of abdomen, left lateral (Florida, USA). Scale bars: 0.25 mm (A, B), 0.5 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.966.55192.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450942" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">18D</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="946C4DED0A7CD7F92349E65957129D3E" author="Bickel, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum Occasional Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="14 - 20" refId="B6" refString="Bickel, DJ, 2000. New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Bishop Museum Occasional Papers 64: 14 - 20" title="New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." volume="64" year="2000">Bickel 2000</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1a) but in 
<taxonomicName id="A920B37680ED7D2198A67AC568C6BF86" genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="E4C370B680A206DBC9F096D8C7A9E50B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the surtylus is smaller and pointed apically and the phallus is not serrate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8ECFCE1338501A2EACB1702DF512F96E" captionStart="Figure 18" captionStartId="F18" captionText="Figure 18. Tarsus I and terminalia of males A Achradocera apicalis (Aldrich), tarsus I, posterior view (Montserrat) B Achradocera barbata (Loew), tarsus I, posterior view (Kentucky, USA), arrows indicate ventral setae C Achradocera apicalis, tip of abdomen, left lateral (Montserrat) D Achradocera barbata, tip of abdomen, left lateral (Florida, USA). Scale bars: 0.25 mm (A, B), 0.5 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.966.55192.figure18" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/450942" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">18C</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="5E7383F329C19C790D05CE1FA0D768F0" author="Bickel, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum Occasional Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="14 - 20" refId="B6" refString="Bickel, DJ, 2000. New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Bishop Museum Occasional Papers 64: 14 - 20" title="New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." volume="64" year="2000">Bickel 2000</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 1e as 
<taxonomicName id="BF6FB4DCF9B6B5DCE739BE9DA81651BE" genus="A." lsidName="A. barbata" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="barbata">
<emphasis id="C41E09FAA41C53E95BF4F9E9DCDCE96D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. barbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The antennal length in males of 
<taxonomicName id="D38886E75D9C4FAF651F3ED98505EFDC" genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="F1BC2EC0F576A9CE2C57B9B10256F3C4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is highly variable, as noted by 
<bibRefCitation id="54CF912416B61270E4A12AC49405886B" author="Bickel, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum Occasional Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="14 - 20" refId="B6" refString="Bickel, DJ, 2000. New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Bishop Museum Occasional Papers 64: 14 - 20" title="New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." volume="64" year="2000">Bickel (2000)</bibRefCitation>
, but in all available specimens is distinctly shorter than the antenna in males of 
<taxonomicName id="4A6170B4C967DA550513E4F39BAFE689" genus="A." lsidName="A. barbata" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="barbata">
<emphasis id="F33C24F3C511C2DAD2F528AE70F70753" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. barbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, 
<taxonomicName id="CB89613BE4A4221387C4C369A37BC2AA" genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="345B9E305738744C4B74A5C86C88A790" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Aldrich) is here removed from synonymy with 
<taxonomicName id="AE96F8FBBC22F1DD56D8E7CEB28380A2" genus="A." lsidName="A. barbata" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="barbata">
<emphasis id="B831B479687650D47F3EC418A677A768" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. barbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Loew). The species described in 
<bibRefCitation id="0B5D54C2FB945496FFD3CADBACF0EA30" author="Bickel, DJ" journalOrPublisher="Bishop Museum Occasional Papers" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" pagination="14 - 20" refId="B6" refString="Bickel, DJ, 2000. New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae). Bishop Museum Occasional Papers 64: 14 - 20" title="New World Achradocera in Hawai'i, Tonga, and French Polynesia, with discussion of the genus (Diptera: Dolichopodidae)." volume="64" year="2000">Bickel (2000)</bibRefCitation>
as 
<taxonomicName id="5E460EFFD337070211A3E993498A2FF2" genus="A." lsidName="A. barbata" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="barbata">
<emphasis id="B921A512E04B725EE3CC02F2643CEF98" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. barbata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is 
<taxonomicName id="F9CEFFE7A3C802813904C50A4F49CF84" genus="A." lsidName="A. apicalis" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" rank="species" species="apicalis">
<emphasis id="A4C2F703708018FC560EF088FABECE1F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">A. apicalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
